#: app/Admin/Offers/OfferEditPage.php:1143
msgid "A checkout bump is a last-step add-on shown on checkout before Place order. Shoppers can add it without leaving checkout. It appears when the offer is active, its rules match the current cart or checkout context, and the offered product is available."
msgstr ""

#: app/Admin/Offers/OfferEditPage.php:1144
msgid "A product page offer is a related add-on shown near the add-to-cart area on matching product pages. It helps shoppers add a complementary item while considering a product. It appears when the offer is active, the viewed product matches your rules, and the offered product is available."
msgstr ""

#: app/Admin/Offers/OfferEditPage.php:1145
msgid "A cart offer is a cross-sell shown while shoppers review their cart. It recommends an extra item before they continue to checkout. It appears when the offer is active, the current cart matches your rules, and the offered product is available."
msgstr ""

#: app/Admin/Offers/OfferEditPage.php:1146
msgid "A thank-you follow-on offer is a post-purchase offer shown on the order received page after the main order is complete. It sends shoppers to a separate checkout for the extra item. It appears when the offer is active, the completed order matches your rules, and the offered product is available."
msgstr ""

